edium to high priority issue for druid spells.<br><br>-Quelm, 58 Preserver<br>Drunken Tsunami, Terris-Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=felessan>Felessan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/17/01 5:52:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2636.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blizzard</span><hr size=1> As of a patch a few months? ago, rain spells have been able to deal the killing blow.  <br><br>I love this spell - but pity the fire beetle who walks past Sergeant Slate as I'm nuking him down with it &lt;grin&gt; <p>Felessan<BR>Wood-elf wanderer of the Fourth Wall<br>Tarew Marr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquelm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quelm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wolf Elemental</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/17/01 6:42:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2636.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blizzard</span><hr size=1> From personal experience, there's a dramatically increased resist rate when a mob is near death.  In a month or two of using this spell, I have yet to see it land the killing blow on anything other than a MOB's pet.  I've tested this in Chardok, Sebilis, Fungus Grove and the Grey - mobs will not die to Blizzard.  Granted, my sample size isn't very large, perhaps 15 casts of the spell when the MOB is snare-dumb, just to test.  I've seen many hit/hit/resist combinations as a mob approaches death.<br><br>Killshots are fun.  I joke around with wizards and try for the killing nuke once in a while.  I notice who kills mobs, and it hasn't been me with Blizzard.<br><br>That said, I'd like to hear other recent personal experiences with the spell, or official word from big V.<br><br>-Quelm, 58 Preserver<br>Drunken Tsunami, Terris-Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaffe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Affe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/26/01 9:42:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2636.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blizzard</span><hr size=1> Blizzard is still incapable of dealing the killing blow. I've been using this spell all over Luclin the last week and have not seen it once deal the kill shot.<br><br>If other classes rain spells were fixed a few months ago then VI obviously forgot to fix Blizzard.  A shame as this is can be a druid's most efficient means of dealing damage. <p>-Affe</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulotusflystewnicely.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lotusfly Stewnicely</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/28/01 3:53:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2636.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.prexus.com/ef/becky/snap.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Blizzard</span><hr size=1> A wonderful spell - for a wildfire level of mana, you can nuke for 100-150% of wildfire damage.  It's fantastic, and I am surprised how rarely used this spell seems to be amongst druids.<br><br>Increasing my DD output by 100-150% is a good thing, in my books! :)<br><br>As cautioned above, cast this spell so that it completes before the party gets the target below 500 HPs in order to avoid the mandatory final resistance.<br><br>The particularly keen druid might even use the 49 spell &quot;Fire&quot; to debuff the mob's Cold Resist by 50.  Again, it is surprising to hear that many druids don't know that they can sunder cold-style, even if for a short duration (3 ticks).  ;)<br><br><br>Toodlepip, <p><img src="http://www.prexus.com/ef/becky/kitty.gif" align="right">--<br><b><a href="http://www.suckbird.com/roster/profile.asp?who=Lotusfly">Lotusfly Stewnicely</a></b><br><b><a href="http://www.keepersofthefaith.org" style="text-decoration: none">KTF</a></b>, <b>Prexus</b><br><a href ="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=37093" style="text-decoration: none">Magelo Profile</a><br><br><i>A small mind is a tidy mind</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uperkynipples.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Perk Ynipples</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/1/02 5:21:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2636.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blizzard</span><hr size=1> In small groups (ie when the mob isn't dead before I can cast =) I love chaining RFS, Fire, Blizzard, and Frost...  takes a lot of spell gems, but you can do hella damage... even more fun if you have a few mobs close together so you can take advantage of the small radius AoE on Fire and the extra pulse from Blizzard... against two mobs, Blizzard has the potential to do 2k damage for 330 mana... not shabby at all... Not on the same level as wizard or mage rains, but not to bad... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showMessage?topicID=2623.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showMessage?topicID=2602.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2636.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.execpc.com/~msippel/thedruidsgrove/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.emailToFriend?topicID=2636.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.threadControl?topicID=2636.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2636.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2636.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=po